<li><a href="http://www.btinternet.com/~britishempire/empire/empire.htm" class="external text" title="http://www.btinternet.com/~britishempire/empire/empire.htm" rel="nofollow">British Empire</a></li>
<li><a href="http://www.cato.org/pubs/pas/pa-459es.html" class="external text" title="http://www.cato.org/pubs/pas/pa-459es.html" rel="nofollow">The Empire Strikes Out: The "New Imperialism" and Its Fatal Flaws by Ivan Eland, director of defense policy studies at the Cato Institute.</a> (an article comparing contemporary defense policy with those of New Imperialism (1870-1914)</li>
<li><a href="http://www.angelfire.com/nb/martian/newimp.htm" class="external text" title="http://www.angelfire.com/nb/martian/newimp.htm" rel="nofollow">The Martian Chronicles: History Behind the Chronicles New Imperialism 1870-1914</a></li>
<li>1- Coyne, Christopher J. and Steve Davies. "Empire: Public Goods and Bads" (Jan 2007). <a href="http://www.econjournalwatch.org/pdf/CoyneDaviesCommentJanuary2007.pdf" class="external autonumber" title="http://www.econjournalwatch.org/pdf/CoyneDaviesCommentJanuary2007.pdf" rel="nofollow">[3]</a></li>
<li><a href="http://www.fordham.edu/halsall/mod/modsbook34.html" class="external free" title="http://www.fordham.edu/halsall/mod/modsbook34.html" rel="nofollow">http://www.fordham.edu/halsall/mod/modsbook34.html</a></li>
<li><a href="http://www.columbia.edu/~lt95/altlect14.htm" class="external free" title="http://www.columbia.edu/~lt95/altlect14.htm" rel="nofollow">http://www.columbia.edu/~lt95/altlect14.htm</a> (a course syllabus)</li>
<li><a href="http://www.gpc.edu/~proseman/Imperialism.htm" class="external text" title="http://www.gpc.edu/~proseman/Imperialism.htm" rel="nofollow">The 19th Century: The New Imperialism</a></li>
<li><a href="http://www.leftturnbooks.com/4000-008.html" class="external text" title="http://www.leftturnbooks.com/4000-008.html" rel="nofollow">Marxism and The New Imperialism by Alex Callinicos, John Rees, Chris Harman, and Mike Haynes</a></li>
<li>2- Coyne, Christopher J. and Steve Davies. "Empire: Public Goods and Bads" (Jan 2007). <a href="http://www.econjournalwatch.org/pdf/CoyneDaviesCommentJanuary2007.pdf" class="external autonumber" title="http://www.econjournalwatch.org/pdf/CoyneDaviesCommentJanuary2007.pdf" rel="nofollow">[4]</a></li>
